dcterms:description: The IEEE 10-machine 39-node system is a well-known regional transmission system network used for fault detection in power grids. It consists of 39 buses, including 10 generator buses and 19 load buses, and is widely utilized for various analyses such as small-signal stability and dynamic stability.
dcterms:title: IEEE 10-machine 39-node system
